document HELP {
  title: "SEMDL CLI Help"
  command: "ssd --help --format semdl"
  topic: "root"
  format: "semdl"
}

resource HELP_TOPIC {
  type: help-topic
  label: "root"
}

segment HELP_LINE_1 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "SEMDL CLI Help"
}

segment HELP_LINE_2 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "1. Overview"
}

segment HELP_LINE_3 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd` validates, explains, transforms, and updates `.ssd` and `.ssm` assets."
}

segment HELP_LINE_4 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- This help output is the canonical entrypoint for CLI guidance."
}

segment HELP_LINE_5 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Necessary canonical CLI syntax can be obtained from this help and its topic pages without opening repository files."
}

segment HELP_LINE_6 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Repository artifacts for requirements, acceptance, and formal notation may exist, but they are aligned maintenance assets rather than the user-facing authority."
}

segment HELP_LINE_7 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "2. Table of Contents"
}

segment HELP_LINE_8 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd help overview`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_9 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd help toc`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_10 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd help grammar`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_11 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd help reference [subcommand]`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_12 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd help recipes [topic]`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_13 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd help samples`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_14 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd help troubleshooting`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_15 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "3. Grammar"
}

segment HELP_LINE_16 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Root: `ssd <subcommand> ...`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_17 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Root help: `ssd help [topic] [--format semdl]`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_18 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Targeted reference help: `ssd help reference [subcommand] [--format semdl]`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_19 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Targeted recipe help: `ssd help recipes [topic] [--format semdl]`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_20 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Global help: `ssd --help [--format semdl]`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_21 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Subcommand help: `ssd <subcommand> --help [--format semdl]`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_22 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- This CLI help remains the canonical user-facing operational guide."
}

segment HELP_LINE_23 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "4. Reference"
}

segment HELP_LINE_24 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `check`: validate syntax and references for a document set"
}

segment HELP_LINE_25 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `search`: evaluate a read-only query against document inputs"
}

segment HELP_LINE_26 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `extract`: build an initial semantic document from raw inputs"
}

segment HELP_LINE_27 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `similarity`: compare two semantic targets"
}

segment HELP_LINE_28 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `explain`: show the merged semantic view for an entity id"
}

segment HELP_LINE_29 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `normalize`: canonicalize document shape and output profile"
}

segment HELP_LINE_30 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `add`: add one semantic entity skeleton"
}

segment HELP_LINE_31 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `set`: update one inline or sidecar field"
}

segment HELP_LINE_32 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `remove`: remove one target or fail on unsafe removal"
}

segment HELP_LINE_33 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `annotate`: add rationale/caveat/todo-like notes"
}

segment HELP_LINE_34 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `split`: move sidecar-eligible metadata out of inline form"
}

segment HELP_LINE_35 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `merge`: produce a merged inline view"
}

segment HELP_LINE_36 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `help`: navigate this help system"
}

segment HELP_LINE_37 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "5. Reverse Lookup"
}

segment HELP_LINE_38 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Validate a document: `ssd check <file>`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_39 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Explain an assertion: `ssd explain <id> <file>`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_40 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Preview an inline edit: `ssd set path:<id>.<field> <value> --dry-run <file>`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_41 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Preview a sidecar annotation: `ssd annotate id:<id> rationale <text> --target sidecar --dry-run <file>`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_42 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Machine-readable help: `ssd help grammar --format semdl`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_43 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Understand an option error: `ssd help grammar`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_44 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Understand a selector-layer error: `ssd help recipes wrong-layer`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_45 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "6. Samples"
}

segment HELP_LINE_46 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd check docs/examples/minimal.ssd`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_47 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd explain A1 docs/examples/minimal.ssd`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_48 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd help reference check`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_49 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd check --help --format semdl`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_50 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- `ssd set meta:A1.confidence 0.91 --dry-run docs/examples/minimal.ssd`"
}

segment HELP_LINE_51 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "7. Cautions, Known Bugs, Reporting"
}

segment HELP_LINE_52 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- In this initial slice, `search` supports `select`, an optional single `where`, target-based `similar`, `return: matches`, and grouped `return: subgraph`, including similarity-backed grouped results. `where` accepts presence checks, scalar equality, numeric range comparisons, mixed `and`/`or` boolean expressions, and parenthesized grouping; `not` and function calls remain outside this slice. `extract` supports skeletal raw `.txt` intake, multi-input `--out` aggregation, and explicit `ollama` and `openai` embedding adapters; raw `--stdout` stays single-input and embedding generation requires `--out <output.ssd>`. `ssd similarity` supports pairwise cosine comparison against precomputed embeddings in one input document; `add` supports inline structural kinds plus create-only sidecar `annotation` and `provenance`."
}

segment HELP_LINE_53 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Use `--format semdl` when another tool needs structured help output."
}

segment HELP_LINE_54 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Update flows are acceptance-driven and still incomplete for full file rewriting."
}

segment HELP_LINE_55 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Report problems with the command, argv, input paths, expected output, actual output, and related golden file."
}

segment HELP_LINE_56 {
  source: HELP_TOPIC
  text_quote: "- Preferred reporting path: repository issue or change request with a reproducing CLI case."
}
